The performance takes place on the stage of the {{ill|Bugaku Hall|ja|舞楽殿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bugaku Hall|qq=}}, featuring railings in front of the {{ill|Haiden|ja|拝殿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haiden|qq=}} of the {{ill|Tengū Shrine|ja|天宮神社|1=Ame-no-Miya Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tengū Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Miya Shrine|qq=}}. The dancers include four children, boys around 15 years old, and 11 adults. Accompaniment is provided by large drums, gongs, small drums, and flutes. The repertoire consists of 12 pieces: "Enbu" (延舞), "Iroka" (色香), "Niwa Chō" (庭胡蝶), "Tori-na" (鳥名), "Taihei-raku" (太平楽), "Shin Makka" (新靺鞨), "Ama" (安摩), "Ni no Mai" (二の舞), "Ryōō" (陵王), "Bato" (抜頭), "Nasu" (納曽利), and "Shishi" (獅子).

